*\\n\\nI need to check the classpath to see if there's maybe a source JAR involved. If there’s only one JAR, then there shouldn't be any duplicates, especially in the native setup. I'll use an assertion to confirm that no exception is thrown. This will call `getResources`, which is part of the public API designed to ensure that a class is defined only once. That sounds solid, and I think it’ll work well for my testing purposes!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_WuH4XT6ZBItahChhNH5rTfKE|fc_06f020777a0891b0016a40f9a296648190a5a3011d2fa2b1d3", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/co.elastic.clients/elasticsearch-java/9.0.3/src/test/java/co_elastic_clients/elasticsearch_java/DuplicateResourceFinderTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage co_elastic_clients.elasticsearch_java;\n\nimport co.elastic.clients.util.DuplicateResourceFinder;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThatCode;\n\npublic class DuplicateResourceFinderTest {\n    @Test\n    void acceptsUniqueClientClassOnClasspath() {\n        DuplicateResourceFinder.enableCheck(true);\n\n        assertThatCode(() -> DuplicateResourceFinder.ensureClassUniqueness(DuplicateResourceFinder.class))\n            .doesNotThrowAnyException();\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1455, "output": 739, "cacheRead": 18432, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 20626, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782643094032, "responseId": "resp_06f020777a0891b0016a40f9967c348190b2c4a1c7bfded316"}}
